        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T20:27:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Glad to hear it\u0027s feasible!\n\nI understand this container is uploaded automatically multiple times a day, so I don\u0027t know if it would be practical to update the digest by hand. We can always manually update it upon any significant changes to CanvasKit, Debugger, etc., but an autoroller is probably best in the long term.\n\nIf it makes things any easier, the digest can be imported from a separate, one-line file (e.g. //skia_wasm_digest.bzl) that exports the digest as a constant that can be imported from //WORKSPACE. We could even generate the entire contents of the .bzl file from a string template or something.",
      "parentUuid": "922f472b_5035ee29",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3104,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 3105,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "874d6539860ba34ca19be6c10b925162701d721b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "92d4f76b_1b4af256",
        "filename": "WORKSPACE",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 3105,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-08T20:33:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this container uploaded at every Skia commit?  If so, we\u0027re definitely not going to want that many roll commits in infra.  A nightly roll might be more appropriate.",
      "parentUuid": "94ae3d17_d2710d2b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3104,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 3105,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "874d6539860ba34ca19be6c10b925162701d721b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "49d892cf_63f0a2b2",
        "filename": "WORKSPACE",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 3105,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-15T13:01:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In the current setup, a new container is generated via a Skia commit. A nightly roll could work, but might make the latency of seeing new features roll out on things like jsfiddle.skia.org go from ~30 minutes to ~1 day.\n\nI would lean toward trying a tag like prod/latest at first to see how it goes. If there are troubles with bazel caching (In docker, you can force a pull; can Bazel?) or we run into inconsistency issues (we have not with the current model, AFAIK), then we can re-evaluate.",
      "parentUuid": "92d4f76b_1b4af256",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3104,
        "startChar": 30,
        "endLine": 3105,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "874d6539860ba34ca19be6c10b925162701d721b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b8f7618c_8ca845be",
        "filename": "WORKSPACE",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 3105,
