        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-15T13:01:32Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How is it that this rule doesn\u0027t need to call container_pull? Of note, it appears caching is not enabled by default (https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_docker#container_pull-1) so I don\u0027t think we need to worry as much about caching unreliability.",
      "revId": "874d6539860ba34ca19be6c10b925162701d721b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "0a227d02_1d2d9e94",
        "filename": "infra-sk/index.bzl",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 383,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-12-15T20:50:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We have a container_pull target in the WORKSPACE file named \"skia_wasm\" that pulls the Skia WASM image. The below container_flatten target has a dependency on the output of said container_pull target via the \"image\" attribute (image \u003d \"@skia_wasm//image\"). Bazel will build the container_pull target (i.e. will pull the Skia WASM container), or reuse its cached output, before building the below container_flatten target.\n\nRegarding caching:\n\nI believe the DOCKER_REPO_CACHE environment variable mentioned in the link above controls the internal caching behavior of the container_pull rule. Specifically, where in the file system it will save any layers pulled from the container registry (see [1] and [2]). If we build a container_pull target, clear Bazel\u0027s cache with \"bazel clean\" and build said target again, then presumably the image layers will be read from the DOCKER_REPO_CACHE directory instead of being re-downloaded from the container registry.\n\nThat said, this internal caching behavior is orthogonal to Bazel. Bazel will build a target once and cache its output artifacts. That\u0027s consistent with the behavior I\u0027ve observed while experimenting with these rules locally and against RBE.\n\n[1] https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_docker/blob/e290d0975ab19f9811933d2c93be275b6daf7427/container/pull.bzl#L144\n[2] https://github.com/bazelbuild/rules_docker/blob/e290d0975ab19f9811933d2c93be275b6daf7427/container/go/cmd/puller/puller.go#L48",
      "parentUuid": "cc5cbb9b_ecf81fca",
      "revId": "874d6539860ba34ca19be6c10b925162701d721b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
